==Dutch==

'''zijn + aan het + infinitive'''
*'''Aan het''' is part of a construction in Dutch to form the [[w:continuous aspect|continuous aspect]]. The construction is set up by using the regular conjugation of the auxiliary verb '''[[zijn]]''' (to be), followed by '''aan het''' and the infinitive form of the verb describing the action. Below are a few examples:

#{''ik ben aan het eten'' --- I am eating}, as opposed to {''ik eet'' --- I eat},
#{''ik was aan het eten'' --- I was eating}, as opposed to {''ik at'' --- I ate}.